siteMetadata.title: Humbly Created Co. | Charleston Wedding Videography

content.value: Ben & Katie, I love you guys. Getting to video friends tie the knot is so special. Especially because I can look back in their relationship and see evidence of care and love for one another that is built on a solid foundation. These Jesus lovin', adventure seeking, Gamecock supporting people will always be near and dear to me.

Jason & Kim, are the type of people that we all want and need in our lives. They exude energy, love, and compassion in ways that leave you feeling known and cared for. Seeing them say, "I do" was special, but hearing every intentional word from their vows reminded me of the beauty and gift of marriage.

There were so many emotional loving moments between Brittany and Andy that made this Charleston plantation wedding special. This wedding had all the elements to make it picturesque: An extensive tree lined entrance, a teary-eyed groom as he watched his bride walk down the aisle, a 1960s vintage Ford Mustang final exit and so much more. Congratulations Andy and Brittany!

From the moment I got to encounter Ali's bubbly, vivacious personality and Oliver's cool and playful persona, I knew that their wedding was bound to be SO much fun. And to top it off Oliver's family and friends from London flew down in full force to be a part of the occasion which made this beautiful, Houston evening one to remember.
